TechSolutionsHeader 

  BOOKMARK 

Vision Servers

 

Standard Terms and Conditions  

 

 

PLEASE READ CAREFULLY: UNLESS YOU AS THE CUSTOMER HAVE ANOTHER VALID AGREEMENT APPLICABLE TO THIS PURCHASE, OR UNLESS THE HP ELECTRONIC STORE SPECIFIES DIFFERING OR ADDITIONAL TERMS FOR A SPECIFIC PRODUCT OR SUPPORT, THE FOLLOWING VISION CUSTOMER TERMS AND ANY VISION SITE SPECIFIED TERMS WILL GOVERN PURCHASES MADE HEREUNDER.

 

BY USING, DOWNLOADING, INSTALLING, COPYING, OR ACCESSING THE PRODUCT, YOU AGREE TO THE TERMS BELOW. IF YOU ARE ACCEPTING THESE TERMS ON BEHALF OF ANOTHER PERSON OR A COMPANY OR OTHER LEGAL ENTITY, YOU REPRESENT AND WARRANT THAT YOU HAVE FULL AUTHORITY TO BIND THAT PERSON, COMPANY, OR LEGAL ENTITY TO THESE TERMS. IF YOU DO NOT AGREE TO THESE TERMS, AND DELIVERY OF THE PRODUCT OR SUPPORT IS EFFECTED, DO NOT USE, DOWNLOAD, INSTALL, COPY, OR ACCESS THE PRODUCT OR SUPPORT, AND PROMPTLY RETURN THE PRODUCT WITH PROOF OF PURCHASE AND OBTAIN A REFUND OF THE AMOUNT YOU PAID, IF ANY. IF YOU DOWNLOADED ANY SOFTWARE, CONTACT THE PARTY FROM WHOM YOU ACQUIRED IT.

 

Parties. These terms represent the agreement ("Agreement") that governs the purchase of products and services from the Vision Corporation entity identified in the signature section below ("Vision") by the Customer entity identified below ("Customer").

 

Orders. "Order" means the accepted order including any supporting material which the parties identify as incorporated either by attachment or reference ("Supporting Material"). Supporting Material may include (as examples) product lists, hardware or software specifications, standard or negotiated service descriptions, data sheets and their supplements, and statements of work (SOWs), published warranties and service level agreements, and may be available to Customer in hard copy or by accessing a designated Vision website.

 

Order Arrangements. Customer may place orders with Vision through our website, customer-specific portal, or by letter, fax or e-mail. Where appropriate, orders must specify a delivery date. If Customer extends the delivery date of an existing Order beyond ninety (90) days, then it will be considered a new order. Customer may cancel a hardware Order at no charge up to five (5) business days prior to shipment date.

 

Prices and Taxes. Prices will be as quoted in writing by Vision or, in the absence of a written quote, as set out on our website, customer-specific portal, or Vision published list price at the time an order is submitted to Vision. Prices are exclusive of taxes, duties, and fees (including installation, shipping, and handling) unless otherwise quoted.

 

Invoices and Payment. Customer agrees to pay all invoiced amounts within thirty (30) days of Vision's invoice date. Vision may suspend or cancel performance of open Orders or services if Customer fails to make payments when due.

 

Title. Risk of loss or damage and title for hardware products will pass upon delivery to Customer or its designee. Where permitted by law, Vision retains a security interest in products sold until full payment is received.

 

Delivery. Vision will use all commercially reasonable efforts to deliver products in a timely manner. Vision may elect to deliver software and related product/license information by electronic transmission or via download.

 

Installation. If Vision is providing installation with the product purchase, Vision's site guidelines (available upon request) will describe.

 

Customer requirements. Vision will conduct its standard installation and test procedures to confirm completion.

 

Support Services. Vision's support services will be described in the applicable Supporting Material , which will cover the description of Vision's offering, eligibility requirements, service limitations and Customer responsibilities, as well as the Customer systems supported.

 

Eligibility. Vision's service, support and warranty commitments do not cover claims resulting from:

improper use, site preparation, or site or environmental conditions or other non-compliance with applicable Supporting Material; Modifications or improper system maintenance or calibration not performed by Vision or authorized by Vision;

failure or functional limitations of any non-Vision software or product impacting systems receiving Vision support or service;

malware (e.g. virus, worm, etc.) not introduced by Vision; or abuse, negligence, accident, fire or water damage, electrical disturbances, transportation by Customer, or other causes beyond Vision's control.

 

Dependencies. Vision's ability to deliver services will depend on Customer's reasonable and timely cooperation and the accuracy and completeness of any information from Customer needed to deliver the services.

 

Product Performance. All Vision-branded hardware products are covered by Vision's limited warranty statements that are provided with the products or otherwise made available. Hardware warranties begin on the date of delivery or if applicable, upon completion of Vision installation, or (where Customer delays Vision installation) at the latest 30 days from the date of delivery. Non-Vision branded products receive warranty coverage as provided by the relevant third party supplier.

 

Software Performance. Vision warrants that its branded software products will conform materially to their specifications and be free of malware at the time of delivery. Vision warranties for software products will begin on the date of delivery and unless otherwise specified in Supporting Material, will last for ninety (90) days. Vision does not warrant that the operation of software products will be uninterrupted or error-free or that software products will operate in hardware and software combinations other than as authorized by Vision in Supporting Material.

 

Services Performance. Services are performed using generally recognized commercial practices and standards. Customer agrees to provide prompt notice of any such service concerns and Vision will re-perform any service that fails to meet this standard.

 

Product Warranty Claims. When we receive a valid warranty claim for an Vision hardware or software product, Vision will either repair the relevant defect or replace the product. If Vision is unable to complete the repair or replace the product within a reasonable time, Customer will be entitled to a full refund upon the prompt return of the product to Vision (if hardware) or upon written confirmation by Customer that the relevant software product has been destroyed or permanently disabled. Vision will pay for shipment of repaired or replaced products to Customer and Customer will be responsible for return shipment of the product to Vision.

 

Remedies. This Agreement states all remedies for warranty claims. To the extent permitted by law, Vision disclaims all other warranties.

 

Intellectual Property Rights. No transfer of ownership of any intellectual property will occur under this Agreement. Customer grants Vision a non-exclusive, worldwide, royalty-free right and license to any intellectual property that is necessary for Vision and its designees to perform the ordered services.

 

Intellectual Property Rights Infringement. Vision will defend and/or settle any claims against Customer that allege that an Vision-branded product or service as supplied under this Agreement infringes the intellectual property rights of a third party. Vision will rely on Customer's prompt notification of the claim and cooperation with our defense. Vision may modify the product or service so as to be non-infringing and materially equivalent, or we may procure a license. If these options are not available, we will refund to Customer the amount paid for the affected product in the first year or the depreciated value thereafter or, for support services, the balance of any pre-paid amount. Vision is not responsible for claims resulting from any unauthorized use of the products or services.

 

License Grant. Vision grants Customer a non-exclusive license to use the version or release of the Vision-branded software listed in the Order. Permitted use is for internal purposes only (and not for further commercialization), and is subject to any specific software licensing information that is in the software product or its Supporting Material. For non-Vision branded software, the third party's license terms will govern its use.

 

Updates. Customer may order new software versions, releases or maintenance updates ("Updates"), if available, separately or through an Vision software support agreement. Additional licenses or fees may apply for these Updates or for the use of the software in an upgraded environment. Updates are subject to the license terms in effect at the time that Vison makes them available to Customer.

 

License Restrictions. Vision may monitor use/license restrictions remotely and, if Vision makes a license management program available, Customer agrees to install and use it within a reasonable period of time. Customer may make a copy or adaptation of a licensed software product only for archival purposes or when it is an essential step in the authorized use of the software. Customer may use this archival copy without paying an additional license only when the primary system is inoperable. Customer may not copy licensed software onto or otherwise use or make it available on any public external distributed network. Licenses that allow use over Customer's intranet require restricted access by authorized users only. Customer will also not modify, reverse engineer, disassemble decrypt, decompile or make derivative works of any software licensed to Customer under this Agreement unless permitted by statute, in which case Customer will provide Vision with reasonably detailed information about those activities.

 

License Term and Termination. Unless otherwise specified, any license granted is perpetual, provided however that if Customer fails to comply with the terms of this Agreement, Vision may terminate the license upon written notice. Immediately upon termination, or in the case of a limited-term license, upon expiration, Customer will either destroy all copies of the software or return them to Vision, except that Customer may retain one copy for archival purposes only.

 

License Transfer. Customer may not sublicense, assign, transfer, rent or lease the software or software license except as permitted by Vision. Vision-branded software licenses are generally transferable subject to Vision's prior written authorization and payment to Vsion of any applicable fees. Upon such transfer, Customer's rights shall terminate and Customer shall transfer all copies of the software to the transferee. Transferee must agree in writing to be bound by the applicable software license terms. Customer may transfer firmware only upon transfer of associated hardware.

 

License Compliance. Vision may audit Customer compliance with the software license terms. Upon reasonable notice, Vision may conduct an audit during normal business hours (with the auditor's costs being at Vision's expense). If an audit reveals underpayments then Customer will pay to Vision such underpayments. If underpayments discovered exceed five (5) percent of the contract price, Customer will reimburse Vision for the auditor costs.

 

US Federal Government Use. If software is licensed to Customer for use in the performance of a US Government prime contract or subcontract, Customer agrees that consistent with FAR 12.211 and 12.212, commercial computer software, documentation and technical data for commercial items are licensed under HP's standard commercial license.

Global Trade compliance. Products and services provided under these terms are for Customer's internal use and not for further commercialization. If Customer exports, imports or otherwise transfers products and/or deliverables provided under these terms, Customer will be responsible for complying with applicable laws and regulations and for obtaining any required export or import authorizations. Vision may suspend its performance under this Agreement to the extent required by laws applicable to either party.

 

Limitation of Liability. Vision's liability to Customer under this Agreement is limited to the greater of $1,000,000 or the amount payable by Customer to Vision for the relevant Order. Neither Customer nor Vision will be liable for lost revenues or profits, downtime costs, loss or damage to data or indirect, special or consequential costs or damages. This provision does not limit either party's liability for: unauthorized use of intellectual property, death or bodily injury caused by their negligence; acts of fraud; wilful repudiation of the Agreement; nor any liability which may not be excluded or limited by applicable law.

Force Majeure. Neither party will be liable for performance delays nor for non-performance due to causes beyond its reasonable control, except for payment obligations.

 

Termination. Either party may terminate this Agreement on written notice if the other fails to meet any material obligation and fails to remedy the breach within a reasonable period after being notified in writing of the details. If either party becomes insolvent, unable to pay debts when due, files for or is subject to bankruptcy or receivership or asset assignment, the other party may terminate this Agreement and cancel any unfulfilled obligations. Any terms in the Agreement which by their nature extend beyond termination or expiration of the Agreement will remain in effect until fulfilled and will apply to both parties' respective successors and permitted assigns.

 

General. This Agreement represents our entire understanding with respect to its subject matter and supersedes any previous communication or agreements that may exist. Modifications to the Agreement will be made only through a written amendment signed by both parties. The Agreement will be governed by the laws of the country of Vision or the Vision Affiliate accepting the Order and the courts of that locale will have jurisdiction, however, Vision or its Affiliate may, bring suit for payment in the country where the Customer Affiliate that placed the Order is located. Customer and Vision agree that the United Nations Convention on Contracts for the International Sale of Goods will not apply. Claims arising or raised in the United States will be governed by the laws of the state of California, excluding rules as to choice and conflict of law.

 

 

SUPPLEMENTAL DATA SHEET

 

This Supplemental Data Sheet provides additional general requirements and limitations that apply to HP's support offerings, which are set forth in detail in offering-specific datasheets with the exception of those support offerings delivered by HP Software.

 

SERVICE ELIGIBILITY

 

Hardware Support-General Eligibility.  Hardware products must be in good operating condition, as reasonably determined by Vision, to be eligible for placement under support. You must also maintain eligible products at the latest Vision-specified configuration and revision levels.

 

Return to Support. If you allow support to lapse, Vision may charge you additional fees to resume support or require you to perform certain hardware or software upgrades.

 

Use of Proprietary Service Tools.  Vision may require you to use certain hardware and/or software system and network diagnostic and maintenance programs ("Proprietary Service Tools"), as well as certain diagnostic tools that may be included as part of the your system. Proprietary Service Tools are and remain the sole and exclusive property of Vision, and are provided "as is." Proprietary Service Tools may reside on your systems or sites. You may only use the Proprietary Service Tools during the applicable Support coverage period and only as allowed by Vision and you may not sell, transfer, assign, pledge, or in any way encumber or convey the Proprietary Service Tools. Upon termination of Support, you will return the Proprietary Service Tools or allow Vision to remove these Proprietary Service Tools. You will also be required to:

 

  • Allow Vision to keep the Proprietary Service Tools resident on your systems or sites, and assist Vision in running them;
  • Install Proprietary Service Tools, including installation of any required updates and patches;
  • Use the electronic data transfer capability to inform Vision of events identified by the software;
  • If required, purchase Vision-specified remote connection hardware for systems with remote diagnosis service; and
  • Provide remote connectivity through an approved communications line.

 

 

SUPPORT LIMITATIONS

 

Local Availability of Support.  Some offerings, features, and coverage (and related products) may not be available in all countries or areas. In addition, delivery of support outside of the applicable Vision coverage areas may be subject to travel charges, longer response times, reduced restoration or repair commitments, and reduced coverage hours.

 

Version Support.  Unless otherwise agreed by Vision in writing, and for those offerings not delivered by Vision Software, Vision only provides support for the current version and the immediately preceding version of Vision branded software, and provided that Vision branded software is used with hardware or software included in Vision-specified configurations at the specified version level.  "Version" means a release of software that contains new features, enhancements, and/or maintenance updates, or for certain software, a collection of revisions packaged into a single entity and, as such, made available to our customers.

 

Relocation and impact on Support.  Relocation of any products under support is your responsibility and is subject to local availability and fee changes. Reasonable advance notice to Vision may be required to begin support after relocation. For products, any relocation is also subject to the license terms for such products.

 

Multi-vendor Support. Vision provides support for certain non-Vision branded products. The relevant data sheet will specify availability and coverage levels and the support will be provided accordingly, whether or not the non-Vision branded products are under warranty. Vision may discontinue support of non-Vision branded products if the manufacturer or licensor ceases to provide support for them.

 

Modifications. You will allow Vision, at Vision's request, and at no additional charge, to modify products to improve operation, supportability, and reliability, or to meet legal requirements.

 

CUSTOMER RESPONSIBILITIES

 

Site and Product Access. You will provide Vision access to the products covered under support; and if applicable, adequate working space and facilities within a reasonable distance of the products; access to and use of information, customer resources, and facilities as reasonably determined necessary by Vision to service the products; and other access requirements described in the relevant data sheet. If you fail to provide such access, resulting in Vision's inability to provide support, Vision shall be entitled to charge you for the support call at Vision's published service rates. You are responsible for removing any products ineligible for support, as advised by Vision, to allow Vision to perform support. If delivery of support is made more difficult because of ineligible products, Vision will charge you for the extra work at Vision's published service rates.

 

Licenses.  You may purchase available product support for Vision branded products only if you can provide evidence that you have rightfully acquired an appropriate Vision license for the products, and you may not alter or modify the products unless authorized by Vision at any time.

 

Software Support Documentation and Right to Copy.  You may only copy documentation updates if you purchased the right to copy them for the associated products. Copies must include appropriate Vision trademark and copyright notices.

 

Loaner Units. Vision maintains title and you shall have risk of loss or damage for loaner units if provided at Vision's discretion as part of hardware support or warranty services and such units will be returned to Vision without lien or encumbrance at the end of the loaner period.

 

HARDWARE SUPPORT

 

Compatible Cables and Connectors. You will connect hardware products covered under support with cables and connectors (including fiber optics if applicable) that are compatible with the system, according to the manufacturer's operating manual.

 

Data Backup. To reconstruct your lost or altered files, data, or programs, you must maintain a separate backup system or procedure that is not dependent on the products under support.

 

Temporary Workarounds. You will implement temporary procedures or workarounds provided by Vision while Vision works on a permanent solution.

 

Hazardous Environment.  You will notify Vision if you use products in an environment that poses a potential health or safety hazard to Vision employees or subcontractors. Vision may require you to maintain such products under Vision supervision and may postpone service until you remedy such hazards.

 

Authorized Representative. You will have a representative present when Vision provides support at your site.

 

Product List. You will create, maintain and update a list of all products under support including: the location of the products, serial numbers, the Vision-designated system identifiers, and coverage levels.

 

Solution Center Designated Callers.  You will identify a reasonable number of callers, as determined by Vision and Customer ("Designated Callers"), who may access Vision's customer Support call centers ("Solution Centers") or online help tools.

 

Solution Center Caller Qualifications. Designated Callers must be generally knowledgeable and demonstrate technical aptitude in system administration, system management, and, if applicable, network administration and management and diagnostic testing. Vision may review and discuss with you any Designated Caller's experience to determine initial eligibility. If issues arise during a call to the Solution Center that, in Vision's reasonable opinion, may be a result of a Designated Caller's lack of general experience and training, you may be required to replace that Designated Caller. All Designated Callers must have the proper system identifier as provided to you when Support is initiated. Solution Centers may provide support in English or local languages, or both.

 

GENERAL PROVISIONS

 

Cancellation. You may cancel support orders or delete products from support upon thirty (30) days' written notice, unless otherwise agreed in writing. Vision may discontinue support for products and specific support services no longer included in Vision's support offering upon sixty (60) days' written notice, unless otherwise agreed in writing. If you cancel prepaid support, Vision will refund you a pro-rata amount for the unused prepaid support subject to any restrictions or early termination fees as may be set forth in writing.

 

Pricing. Except for prepaid support or if otherwise agreed in writing, Vision may change support prices upon sixty (60) days' written notice.

 

Additional Services.  Additional services performed by Vision at your request, and that are not included in your purchased support, will be chargeable at the applicable published service rates for the country where the service is performed.

 

Replacement Parts.  Parts provided under hardware support may be whole unit replacements, or be new or functionally equivalent to new in performance and reliability and warranted as new. bm_doc_ed_glbl_snpt.name: Global Snippet
bm_doc_ed_glbl_snpt.data:
<!-- ##################### START: global variable declaration ################ --> <xsl:variable name="main_doc" select="/transaction/data_xml/document[@document_var_name='quote_process']/"/> <xsl:variable name="sub_doc" select="/transaction/data_xml" /> <xsl:variable name="outputCurrency" select="$main_doc/outputCurrency_quote" /> <xsl:variable name="conversionRate" select="$main_doc/conversionRate_quote" /> <xsl:variable name="customerLogo" select="concat($XSL_URL_PARAM, '/servlet/ImageServer?', $BM_IMAGESERVER_TOKEN, '&file_type=cmAttachmentAttr&file_id=', $main_doc/customerLogo_quote)" />
<xsl:variable name="watermark"> <xsl:if test="$main_doc/draft_quote='false'"> <xsl:value-of select="concat($XSL_URL_PARAM, '/bmfsweb/',$XSL_COMPANYNAME_PARAM, '/image/Vision/draft_watermark.jpg')"/> </xsl:if> </xsl:variable> <xsl:variable name="watermark2"> <xsl:if test="$main_doc/draft_quote='false'"> <xsl:value-of select="concat($XSL_URL_PARAM, '/bmfsweb/',$XSL_COMPANYNAME_PARAM, '/image/Vision/draft_watermark2.jpg')"/> </xsl:if> </xsl:variable>
<!-- ********************* START: grouping and category global variables ********** --> <!-- holds values for optional --> <xsl:variable xmlns:str="http://exslt.org/strings" name="optionalArray" select="str:split('false,true,', ',')"/>
<!-- holds the custom group keys, used to get a distinct list of groups --> <xsl:key name="customGroup_keys" match="customGroup_line | miscChargeGroup1_quote | miscChargeGroup2_quote | miscChargeGroup3_quote | miscChargeGroup4_quote | miscChargeGroup5_quote | miscChargeGroup6_quote" use="text()"/>
<xsl:key name="customGroupMisc_keys" match="miscChargeGroup1_quote | miscChargeGroup2_quote | miscChargeGroup3_quote | miscChargeGroup4_quote | miscChargeGroup5_quote | miscChargeGroup6_quote" use="text()"/>
<!-- to cut down on typing creates booleans below --> <xsl:variable name="groupsExist" select="count($sub_doc/document[(@data_type=2 or @data_type= 3) and customGroup_line !='' ])> 0" />
<!-- Misc 1 --> <xsl:variable name="misc1Exists" select="$main_doc/miscChargeProd1_quote != ''" /> <xsl:variable name="isNotOptionalMisc1" select="$main_doc/miscOptional1_quote = 'false'" /> <xsl:variable name="misc1Optional" select="$main_doc/miscOptional1_quote" /> <!-- Misc 2 --> <xsl:variable name="misc2Exists" select="$main_doc/miscChargeProd2_quote != ''" /> <xsl:variable name="isNotOptionalMisc2" select="$main_doc/miscOptional2_quote = 'false'" /> <xsl:variable name="misc2Optional" select="$main_doc/miscOptional2_quote" /> <!-- Misc 3 --> <xsl:variable name="misc3Exists" select="$main_doc/miscChargeProd3_quote != ''" /> <xsl:variable name="isNotOptionalMisc3" select="$main_doc/miscOptional3_quote = 'false'" /> <xsl:variable name="misc3Optional" select="$main_doc/miscOptional3_quote" /> <!-- Misc 4 --> <xsl:variable name="misc4Exists" select="$main_doc/miscChargeProd4_quote != ''" /> <xsl:variable name="isNotOptionalMisc4" select="$main_doc/miscOptional4_quote = 'false'" /> <xsl:variable name="misc4Optional" select="$main_doc/miscOptional4_quote" />
<!-- Misc 5 --> <xsl:variable name="misc5Exists" select="$main_doc/miscChargeProd5_quote != ''" /> <xsl:variable name="isNotOptionalMisc5" select="$main_doc/miscOptional5_quote = 'false'" /> <xsl:variable name="misc5Optional" select="$main_doc/miscOptional5_quote" /> <!-- Misc 6 --> <xsl:variable name="misc6Exists" select="$main_doc/miscChargeProd6_quote != ''" /> <xsl:variable name="isNotOptionalMisc6" select="$main_doc/miscOptional6_quote = 'false'" /> <xsl:variable name="misc6Optional" select="$main_doc/miscOptional6_quote" />
<!-- holds whether or not optionals exist --> <xsl:variable name="optionalExists" select="count($sub_doc/document[@data_type=3 and optional_line='true']) > 0 or not($isNotOptionalMisc1) or not($isNotOptionalMisc2) or not($isNotOptionalMisc3) or not($isNotOptionalMisc4) or not($isNotOptionalMisc5) or not($isNotOptionalMisc6)" />
<!-- ensures that ungrouped items show, figures out if any exist --> <xsl:variable name="ungroupedCountIsOptional" select="count( $sub_doc/document[(@data_type=3 and customGroup_line='' and optional_line='true') or (@data_type=0 and ( ( miscChargeGroup1_quote = '' and $misc1Exists and not($isNotOptionalMisc1) ) or ( miscChargeGroup2_quote = '' and $misc2Exists and not($isNotOptionalMisc2) ) or ( miscChargeGroup3_quote = '' and $misc3Exists and not($isNotOptionalMisc3) ) or ( miscChargeGroup4_quote = '' and $misc4Exists and not($isNotOptionalMisc4) ) or ( miscChargeGroup5_quote = '' and $misc5Exists and not($isNotOptionalMisc5) ) or ( miscChargeGroup6_quote = '' and $misc6Exists and not($isNotOptionalMisc6) ) ))]) "/>
<xsl:variable name="ungroupedCountIsNotOptional" select="count( $sub_doc/document[(@data_type=3 and customGroup_line='' and optional_line='false') or (@data_type=0 and ( ( miscChargeGroup1_quote = '' and $misc1Exists and $isNotOptionalMisc1 ) or ( miscChargeGroup2_quote = '' and $misc2Exists and $isNotOptionalMisc2 ) or ( miscChargeGroup3_quote = '' and $misc3Exists and $isNotOptionalMisc3 ) or ( miscChargeGroup4_quote = '' and $misc4Exists and $isNotOptionalMisc4 ) or ( miscChargeGroup5_quote = '' and $misc5Exists and $isNotOptionalMisc5 ) or ( miscChargeGroup6_quote = '' and $misc6Exists and $isNotOptionalMisc6 ) ))]) "/> <!-- ********************* END: grouping and category global variables ********** -->
<!-- ##################### END: global variable declaration ################ -->
<!-- ##################### START TEMPLATE: GetCustomGroupPosition ################ --> <xsl:template name="getCustomGroupPosition"> <xsl:param name="miscNumber" /> <xsl:param name="numLineItems" />
<xsl:param name="misc1Condition" /> <xsl:param name="misc2Condition" /> <xsl:param name="misc3Condition" /> <xsl:param name="misc4Condition" /> <xsl:param name="misc5Condition" /> <xsl:param name="misc6Condition" />
<xsl:variable name="customGrpCount1"> <xsl:choose> <xsl:when test="$misc1Condition and $miscNumber >= 1">1</xsl:when>
<xsl:otherwise>0</xsl:otherwise> </xsl:choose> </xsl:variable> <xsl:variable name="customGrpCount2"> <xsl:choose> <xsl:when test="$misc2Condition and $miscNumber >= 2">1</xsl:when> <xsl:otherwise>0</xsl:otherwise>
</xsl:choose> </xsl:variable> <xsl:variable name="customGrpCount3"> <xsl:choose> <xsl:when test="$misc3Condition and $miscNumber >= 3">1</xsl:when> <xsl:otherwise>0</xsl:otherwise> </xsl:choose> </xsl:variable>
<xsl:variable name="customGrpCount4"> <xsl:choose> <xsl:when test="$misc4Condition and $miscNumber >= 4">1</xsl:when> <xsl:otherwise>0</xsl:otherwise> </xsl:choose> </xsl:variable> <xsl:variable name="customGrpCount5"> <xsl:choose>
<xsl:when test="$misc5Condition and $miscNumber >= 5">1</xsl:when> <xsl:otherwise>0</xsl:otherwise> </xsl:choose> </xsl:variable> <xsl:variable name="customGrpCount6"> <xsl:choose> <xsl:when test="$misc6Condition and $miscNumber >= 6">1</xsl:when>
<xsl:otherwise>0</xsl:otherwise> </xsl:choose> </xsl:variable>
<xsl:value-of select="$numLineItems + $customGrpCount1 + $customGrpCount2 + $customGrpCount3 + $customGrpCount4 + $customGrpCount5 + $customGrpCount6"/> </xsl:template> <!-- ##################### END TEMPLATE: GetCustomGroupPosition ################ -->
<!-- ##################### START TEMPLATE: GetMiscQty ################ --> <xsl:template name="getMiscQty"> <xsl:param name="qty"/> <xsl:choose> <xsl:when test="number(substring-after($qty, '.')) > 0"> <xsl:value-of select="$qty" /> </xsl:when> <xsl:otherwise> <xsl:value-of select="substring-before($qty, '.')" /> </xsl:otherwise> </xsl:choose> </xsl:template> <!-- ##################### END TEMPLATE: GetMiscQty ################ -->
